[/asy]<answer>It says area is $ 40 $, and it took away $ 10 $ from the area of square $ABCD$, which is $10^2=100$, so $ 100 - 40 = 60 $ square units were taken away, and those $60$ must be the diagonal times the base, which is $ (5\sqrt 4) \times x $ in this diagram. So, $ (5\sqrt 4) \times x = 60 $, and $ x = \frac{60}{5\sqrt2}$.
